Systems tracks etc..description: OD, BIFS, OCI tracks may be present

IOD box.description: An initial object descriptor is present in an IOD box

Single BIFS + IOD.description: Simple scene (IOD plus a BIFS track)

BIFS + OD.description: Simple sub-scene (OD in the IOD box, BIFS track)

implied length.description: (size=0) Box with the length running to end of file (last box)

UUID box.description: A user box using a UUID type (should be ignored if not recognized)

unknown box.description: A box with an 'unknown' code is present in the file and should be ignored. The box type used for testing could be one of 'junk', 'mess', etc.

normal order.description: (moov-mdat) Boxes in the 'usual' order for reading, and in the recommended order inside

late order.description: (mdat first) The 'mdat' first and the 'moov' late, and boxes in the 'moov' in funny order.

64bit headers.description: There are 64-bit versions of the movie, track, and media headers, that allow long durations and dates after 2040.

track enabled flag.description: The track-enabled flag in the track header.

edit list.description: An edit list is used on at least one track, and some material in the media is edited out.

video track.description: There is a video track with video headers

audio track.description: There is an audio track with audio headers

volumetric track.description: There is a volumetric video track

unknown track.description: An unknown type of track should be ignored (handler='junk' etc.)

unknown codec.description: An unknown audio or video codec is used (sample entry name is 'junk' etc.)

image track.description: (no sync table) A track with a single image in it.

data reference.description: Data reference atoms using URLs or URNs are used to refer to media in other files.

64bit chunks.description: The 64-bit version of the chunk offset table is used, and the chunk offsets have non-zero bits in their upper 32 bits.

pad bits.description: At least one track (audio, probably) has a padding bits table for non byte-lengthed Aus

degradation priority.description: A degradation priority table is used (note that the meaning of the priority values is not established by standard).

Protected basic.description: Basic protected streams (e.g. ISMA or OMA) are present

Protected IPMP.description: Protected streams using the IPMP protection boxes are present

sample scale box.description: The sample scale box (presenting video hint) is present

progressive download box.description: The progressive download hitn box is present

Interleaved data.description: The media data is interleaved on a sensible scale (e.g. .5 second) and in order

multiple mdats.description: two or more mdat boxes are present

sample dependency.description: The sample dependency table is present

multiple sample descriptions.description: There is one track ujsing several sample entries, not just one

64bit fragments.description: Fragments are used in combination with 64-bit offsets

basic protected metadata.description: Some meta-data is protected using the basic techniques

ipmp protected metadata.description: Some meta-data is protected using IPMP boxes

metadata references.description: Some meta-data is in external files and linked by data references

item naming.description: Some items use the item information (name etc.) box

RTP hint tracks.description: Regular RTP hint tracks are present. They should be ignored for local playback.

hint track setup.description: Hint track headers etc. are present

sdp boxes.description: (moov and track) SDP information (in user-data) is present

RTP immediate constructor.description: The various forms of packet constructors are tested.

RTP sample contructor with track referen.description: The various forms of packet constructors are tested.

RTP sample contructor on self track.description: The various forms of packet constructors are tested.

RTP sampleDescription constructor.description: The various forms of packet constructors are tested.

avc1 sample entry.description: Simple AVC streams using parameter sets in the sample entry

layering and subseq grps.description: Sample groups are used for layering and sub-sequences

switch tracks.description: Tracks for switch pictures are present, with their track references

separate param stream.description: A separate parameter set stream is used.
